## Avoid Deep Nesting

Too many nested levels make code hard to follow. Consider using logical operators (`&&`, `||`) to combine conditions, or restructure with early returns.

For example, the above could be:
```php
if ($age >= 18 && $hasID) {
    echo "You can enter.";
} elseif ($age >= 18) {
    echo "You need ID.";
} else {
    echo "Too young.";
}
```
